data.title: James Foley: Movies, Photos, Videos, News, Biography & Birthday
data.meta_description: James Foley: Check out the list of all James Foley movies along with photos, videos, biography and birthday. Also find latest James Foley news on Times of India.
data.text:
Reese Witherspoon reveals how a sex scene with Mark Wahlberg in Fear made her very uncomfortable; says, 'I didn’t have control over it'

etimes.in / Jul 14, 2023, 15:35 (IST)

Reese Witherspoon, best known for her appearances in Cruel Intentions and Legally Blonde, recently admitted that she was quite uncomfortable with a sequence in the 1996 film, Fear, which she had no control over. In this scene, she had to have sex with her co-star Mark Wahlberg and during the scene, her character had to orgasm while riding on a roller-coaster.

Aafia Siddiqui: Pakistani prisoner at centre of Texas siege

AFP / Jan 16, 2022, 14:40 (IST)

Aafia Siddiqui, a Pakistani prisoner in the United States whose release was reportedly demanded by a Texas hostage-taker this weekend, is serving an 86-year sentence for the attempted murder of American soldiers.

Virtual reality to bring 'Fifty Shades Darker' to life

PTI / Oct 17, 2016, 13:40 (IST)

James Foley, director of 'Fifty Shades Darker' and 'Fifty Shades Freed', says that virtual reality will be incorporated into the marketing for the latest movie sequel.

Unesco director general denounces murder of journalist James Foley

TNN / Aug 21, 2014, 12:40 (IST)

Unesco director general, Irina Bokova, condemned the murder of American journalist James Foley on Thursday. Foley was kidnapped in Syria in November 2012. A video of his execution was posted on the internet.

'Fifty Shades of Grey' sequels to be shot back-to-back 'Fifty

PTI / Nov 13, 2015, 14:12 (IST)

Universal Pictures is putting "Fifty Shades of Grey" sequels on fast lane and the movies will be shot back-to-back next year with James Foley directing both installments.

Dakota Johnson: Next 'Fifty Shades' film to start shooting in 2016

PTI / Sep 20, 2015, 14:03 (IST)

Actress Dakota Johnson has revealed the production of the second instalment of the popular "Fifty Shades of Grey" trilogy will begin sometime in 2016.

Obama says he has no strategy to deal with ISIS amid reports of waterboarding

TNN / Aug 30, 2014, 05:53 (IST)

US President Barack Obama conceded on Thursday that his administration did not have a strategy yet to combat the extremist Islamic State in Iraq and Syria (ISIS)

2 FIRs against Teesta for 'inflammatory post'

TNN / Aug 24, 2014, 02:01 (IST)

In Ghatlodia, Raju Patel, a resident of Ghatlodia, has registered a complaint against Teesta.In his complaint, he has mentioned that he came across the news and image on his Facebook page and it offended him.

ISIS beyond anything we have seen: US

TNN / Aug 23, 2014, 05:27 (IST)

The Obama administration has signaled what is virtually a new phase in the "war on terror" — a Bush-era expression it had disdained — by pledging to go after the so-called Islamic State terrorists, whether in Iraq or Syria, even if it means putting its campaign against Syrian dictator Bashar Al Assad on the backburner.

US may expand operations against Islamic State in Iraq

TNN / Aug 22, 2014, 03:56 (IST)

The immediate focus of US and British attention has now turned to the man now known as "John the Executioner," the terrorist who ripped a knife across Foley neck and executed him for what he said the US attacks on the Islamic state and its Muslim people.
